    <h1>Dog Care Tips</h1>
    <p>Welcome to our Dog Care Tips page. Here, you'll find basic guidelines and advice on how to take good care of your furry friend. For more detailed information, please refer to the provided links.</p>

    <h2>Feeding Your Dog</h2>
    <p>Ensure you're feeding your dog a balanced diet suitable for their age, size, and activity level. Consult with your vet for personalized advice. <a href="https://www.akc.org/expert-advice/nutrition/">More on feeding your dog.</a></p>

    <h2>Exercise</h2>
    <p>Regular exercise is crucial for your dog's physical and mental health. The amount of exercise needed can vary greatly with breed and size. <a href="https://www.aspca.org/pet-care/dog-care/common-dog-behavior-issues/exercise">Learn more about exercising your dog.</a></p>

    <h2>Regular Vet Visits</h2>
    <p>Annual check-ups are important to monitor your dog's health and catch any issues early. Vaccinations and preventative treatments for parasites are also crucial. <a href="https://www.avma.org/resources-tools/pet-owners/petcare/dog-care">More on dog healthcare.</a></p>

    <h2>Grooming</h2>
    <p>Regular grooming keeps your dog clean and comfortable, and it's also an opportunity to check for any signs of skin problems or parasites. The grooming needs can vary by breed. <a href="https://www.akc.org/expert-advice/health/dog-grooming-tips/">Grooming tips for dogs.</a></p>
